<!-- Core Philosophy -->
<section class="py-16 px-4">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Why It's Built This Way</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      The simplicity <strong class="text-gray-200">IS</strong> the lesson. Every architectural choice in SwarmPod is deliberate, designed to reflect how modern, high-performing teams ship software.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-folk-blue">Multi-Repo Architecture</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400">Each concern lives in its own repository. This is how real teams ship software, enabling independent development and deployment cycles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-folk-green">Modular Gems</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400">SwarmPod Core is a Ruby gem, not a monolithic feature. This promotes reusability and clean separation of concerns.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-folk-purple">Secrets Outside the Repo</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400">Your credentials and API keys never touch version control. SwarmPod enforces best practices for secrets management from the very beginning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-folk-orange">Containerized Environments</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400">Docker Compose makes "works on my machine" a guarantee, not an excuse. Every developer gets an identical, consistent environment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-gray-800/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-folk-blue">Template-Driven Setup</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400">One command creates a consistent starting point for every team member. This eliminates configuration drift and dramatically speeds up onboarding.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-folk-blue/10 to-folk-green/10 rounded-xl border border-gray-700">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">
        You just ran <code class="bg-gray-800 text-folk-green px-2 py-1 rounded">rails new --template</code> and had a working app. That's <strong class="text-white">agentic programming</strong> — letting tools do the setup work so you can focus on what truly matters: building.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

